HEADWORD: Indocible
<hw>In*doc"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indocibilis</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Docible</er>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being taught, or not easily
instructed; dull in intellect; intractable; unteachable; indocile.</def>
<au>Bp. Hall.</au> -- <wordforms><wf>In*doc"i*ble*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indocile</ent>⟦br⟧
